dren and youth should be, how to prepare teachers for the profession, what pedagogical approaches make the most sense given societal trends, and how to reconstruct the purposes of school. This first book-length study of Dewey's extraordinary text attests to the continued power in his work and to the diverse audience of educators to whom he has long appealed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aEducationxAims and objectives. 0aEducationxPhilosophy. 4aEducation : Curriculum. 7aEDUCATION / Philosophy, Theory & Social Aspects.2bisacsh1 aBiesta, Gert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeiman-Nemser, Sharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFenstermacher, Gary D, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHansen, David T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHansen, David T., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHickman, Larry A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKliebard, Herbert M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMinnich, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPage, Reba N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaito, Naoko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791480946423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791480946/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles